## Proposed Chart Change: cluster-manager — Controllable Istio Sidecar Wait
##
## Problem:
##   templates/configmap-m2m-credentials.yaml hardcodes wait_for_istio_sidecar()
##   in main(). The script uses "set -euo pipefail", so when Istio is disabled
##   the function returns 1 and kills the entire job. The job retries 15 times,
##   each waiting 60s for a sidecar that will never come.
##
## Fix: 3 files need to change
## ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. values.yaml — add istio.enabled under credentialsM2M

--- a/charts/cluster-manager/values.yaml
+++ b/charts/cluster-manager/values.yaml
@@ credentialsM2M section
 credentialsM2M:
   enabled: true
+  istio:
+    enabled: true          # Set false when Istio sidecar injection is disabled
+    sidecarWaitTimeout: 60 # Seconds to wait for sidecar readiness
   job:
     terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 90
     backoffLimit: 15


### 2. templates/configmap-m2m-credentials.yaml — make Istio wait conditional

--- a/charts/cluster-manager/templates/configmap-m2m-credentials.yaml
+++ b/charts/cluster-manager/templates/configmap-m2m-credentials.yaml
@@ in the data.credentials-m2m.sh script, replace the hardcoded values at top:

     # Helm values
     VAULT_ADDR="http://{{ .Values.credentialsM2M.vault.service }}:{{ .Values.credentialsM2M.vault.port }}"
     ...existing values...
+    ISTIO_ENABLED="{{ .Values.credentialsM2M.istio.enabled }}"
+    ISTIO_WAIT_TIMEOUT="{{ .Values.credentialsM2M.istio.sidecarWaitTimeout }}"

@@ replace the wait_for_istio_sidecar() function:

     wait_for_istio_sidecar() {
-        local max_wait=60
+        if [ "$ISTIO_ENABLED" != "true" ]; then
+            log "Istio sidecar injection disabled — skipping wait"
+            return 0
+        fi
+        local max_wait=${ISTIO_WAIT_TIMEOUT:-60}
         local wait_time=0
         log "Waiting for Istio sidecar to be ready..."
         while [ $wait_time -lt $max_wait ]; do
@@ no other changes to the loop body


### 3. templates/job-m2m-credentials.yaml — add sidecar.istio.io/inject annotation

--- a/charts/cluster-manager/templates/job-m2m-credentials.yaml
+++ b/charts/cluster-manager/templates/job-m2m-credentials.yaml
@@ in spec.template.metadata, add annotations:

   template:
     metadata:
+      annotations:
+        sidecar.istio.io/inject: "{{ .Values.credentialsM2M.istio.enabled }}"
       labels:
         app.kubernetes.io/name: cluster-manager


## ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Helmfile usage (values/cluster-manager.yaml.gotmpl):
##
##   credentialsM2M:
##     enabled: true
##     istio:
##       enabled: {{ env "EMF_ENABLE_ISTIO" | default "true" }}
##       sidecarWaitTimeout: 60
##
## This lets helmfile-deploy control Istio behavior per environment without
## needing post-deploy hooks or ConfigMap patches.
## ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
